    bibo:volume "73" ;
    dc:creator "Parnaby, Harry E.; King, Andrew G.; Eldridge, Mark D. B." ;
    dc:date "2021" ;
    dc:title "A New Bat Species from Southwestern Western Australia, Previously Assigned to Gould’s Long-eared Bat Nyctophilus gouldi Tomes, 1858" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412333>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412335>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412341>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412343> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412333>
    dc:description "Figure 3. Bivariate plots (mm) showing overlap in measurements of adult N. holtorum sp. nov. (squares, polygons) and adult N. gouldi sensu stricto (circles). Solid symbols are females, open symbols male: (a), condylo-basal skull length (CON) vs. least inter-temporal breadth (INT); (b) CON vs. mastoid breadth (MASB); (c), CON vs. braincase height (BRH); (d) forearm length (FA) vs. greatest skull length (GSL), and (e) FA vs. length from canine to upper rear molar (CM3)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5412333/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412335>
    dc:description "Figure 4. Relatively greater inflation of the braincase of left, the holotype of N. holtorum sp. nov. (WAM M.64188), compared with N. gouldi (AM M.51228). Both are adult males with equal GSL." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5412335/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412341>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Frontal view of AM M.39811, male, paratype of N. holtorum sp. nov. showing enlarged dorsal snout mound posterior to the noseleaf. Scale 5 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5412341/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5412343>
    dc:description "Figure 6. Distributional records of N. holtorum sp. nov. based onAM and WAM voucher specimens examined (n = 26 localities) and bioregional boundaries of the Interim Biological Regionalization Scheme (IBRS version 7; DSEWPAC, 2012). Regions are: AVW, Avon Wheatbelt; JAF, Jarrah Forests; SWA, Swan Coastal Plain and WAR, Warren." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5412343/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

